Author: johntytorwqafdwqafd
Title: [ANN] FRIENDZ ICO: decentralized peer to peer marketing
Body: Friendz has rules and policies to be respected before publishing contents. Our users cannot decide to post let's say, a picture today, a video tomorrow and then and article (like blogs). Our users participate into campaigns that must be checked and approved before being proposed to the community. Then contents are checked and controlled by the validation system before being published on social networks. The validation system has rules to follow, decided by the client company and to make Friendz policies been respected as well. For example we ban contents that refer to smoking or pornography. The validation system is decentralized and made by the community itself and every content must be checked by many people before the publication. That's our way to avoid that not suitable contents are shared #AdminZ

Author: Aivengo111
Title: [ANN] FRIENDZ ICO: decentralized peer to peer marketing
Body: Verdict Friendz is an established marketing and advertising company with a proven track record. Similar to Rentberry, the team is just incorporating blockchain technology into their platform ‚Äì not starting from scratch.  It‚Äôs impressive that the company has already passed its breakeven point and is profitably running. This should give you confidence that the social, ‚Äúword-of-mouth‚Äù model that the FDZ token is built on is a solid foundation.  Even though the team isn‚Äôt comprised of blockchain experts, they‚Äôve brought on some advisors with significant experience in the space.  Risks     Crowded market. There are a host of companies, both traditional and blockchain-related, in the digital marketing industry. It may be tough for Friendz to continue growing at their current pace in such a saturated space. (-2)     Nothing revolutionary. There‚Äôs no ‚Äúwow‚Äù factor to what Friendz is doing. With ICOs having such a high inherent risk, it may make more sense to look at something tackling a bigger problem. (-2)     The mercy of third-parties. Facebook‚Äôs recent advertising guideline changes and the ever-evolving digital media landscape could hinder Friendz in the long run. (-1)  Growth Potential     Proven idea. Most importantly, Friendz is already successful. Investing in a company that‚Äôs already profitable eliminates a lot of risk. (+6)     Virality. The platform is built around social sharing and virality. As more people use the app and share content, the company should ideally see exponential growth. (+4)     Token terms. The small percentage of tokens allocated to the team and buy-back program give me less suspicion that there‚Äôs any funny business going on. (+2)  Disposition Friendz receives a total score of +7 out of 10. The team, product, and token are solid and look to have minimal downside risk compared to other ICO investments. The company isn‚Äôt trying to drastically change the world through a decentralized internet or financial institution overthrow. Instead, they‚Äôre tackling a fairly large industry that probably won‚Äôt be going anywhere anytime soon.  Although this probably won‚Äôt be a home-run 50x return, it could easily by a solid single or double.   This is a good rating from hacked.com. Here is the proof: https://hacked.com/ico-analysis-friendz/

Body: Also, genuinely asking this: What makes this any different than Steemit? Any smart investor will ask that. Steemit seems rather successful and given what your whitepaper says, it appears that this is very similar to Steemit but only differing in about 2-3 areas. Steemit is already rolling so what's gonna make other people use this instead of Steemit (at least from what you can control) when trying to break away from Facebook or the likes? Assuming you aren't a scam dev team, I know you don't want to be regarded as a clone, yet that will happen once someone familiar with crypto reads the whitepaper. I ask as someone who's invested in the project already because that answer will determine if I hold long term or plan an exit within the next 12 months. Thanks for the time reading this!

Author: johntytorwqafdwqafd
Title: [ANN] FRIENDZ ICO: decentralized peer to peer marketing
Body: As you may read in the whitepaper we are a working company with a validated business model, an app available for mobile (ios and android) and desktop used by a community of 200k people. Last year we had revenues for ‚Ç¨1.2millions and have been working with 200 clients among top multinational brands. We are different as our users are not famous influencers, but normal people that like to use socials for fun. We engage them in using the app and reward them for creating and publishing contents on their personal social profiles. In this way the advertising message is communicated in a more natural and genuine way. What we do is to pur the user into a central position in the digital advertising process, and to let him gain for participating in it. The community management is our core caracteristic #AdminZ

Author: johntytorwqafdwqafd
Title: [ANN] FRIENDZ ICO: decentralized peer to peer marketing
Body: The approval system works with the logics of the blockchain: a network of approvers check every content published and verifies that it follows the campaign's guidelines, is high quality, has the right caption and hashtags and so on. Approvers get rewarded for checkin correctly and are ranked based on the correctness of their approval. Only if the content receives the OK from a sufficient number of approvers, it is published automatically on the user personal social profile and the user gets rewarded as well #AdminZ

Author: johntytorwqafdwqafd
Title: [ANN] FRIENDZ ICO: decentralized peer to peer marketing
Body: We created a decentralized system for approving contents. When users create a content, the must follow the guidelines provided in the description of the activity. Users then upload their content in the app. The content goes through a validation system made by the community itself. Experienced users have access to a dashboard where the can see all the contents uploaded. They have to follow some rules to validate those contents. For example: the contect respect the guidelines, the caption is correct, there are the right hashtags, the picture is bright, not blurred, has a nice framework and so on. Many approvers check the content and judge it. The content passes the approval system if a sufficient number of approvers says that the content respect all the previous requirements. Approvers that checked correctely gain a reward. They are also raked based on the correctness of their judgment: if they make too many mistakes, they are banned from the dashboard and can't approve anymore. The contents that do not follow the guidelines are rejected. The contents that pass the approval system and published automatically on the personal social profile of the user, through KPIs.

Title: [ANN] FRIENDZ ICO: decentralized peer to peer marketing
Body: The content must respect the guidelines provided in the description: some of them refer to the company's brief and other to Friendz policy. Approvers have a list of rules for approving content, such as: the contect respect the guidelines, the caption is correct, there are the right hashtags, the picture is bright, not blurred, has a nice framework and so on. Many approvers check the content and judge it. The content passes the approval system if a sufficient number of approvers says that the content respect all the previous requirements.The content can be rejected a few times, so it is quite easy to get the tokens, but the important thing is that it respect the guidelines, that can be more or less restrictive.
